@$VER: EpicES 1.09 (05/10/02)

@Node Main "EpicES Help: Main Contents"
                      @{B}EpicES V1.09 (05/10/2002)@{UB}

This is EpicEncyclopediaSearch V1.09. An alternative search utility for the
wonderful Epic Interactive Encyclopedia '97.

EpicES was created using Blitz Basic 2.1.

I initially decided to develop this program, because I felt the original
program's search facility lacked the ability to display all matches at once.
The only way to find what you want was to keep pressing the "next" key
combination (ramiga n). Then if you missed the article you were looking for,
you had to repeat the whole process again.

I have also noticed that in the directory "Epic_Encyclopedia:Menufiles/
WORLDinfo/", there are text files on 196 countries, but there is no way of
accessing these files from the encyclopedia.

As well as that, there are more subjects located in the archive
"Epic_Encyclopedia:Menufiles/Vin-archive/People-MESS.LHA". As the name
suggests, the archive mainly contains information on people. Again, there is
no way of accessing this from the encyclopedia. You could copy the contents
of this archive to your hard disk, but the archive is 2.3M in size, which is
about 7M uncompressed! So why not search the archive whilst compressed! After
all, LhA can list and extract single files from an archive.

EpicES gets around all of these problems, and provides a stable Gadtools
interface, for efficient and user-friendly searching.



